    desc: "The natural evolution from still image making to moving image making is at the heart of this course as students look at this evolution from a historical, social, conceptual, and technical perspective. Artists who have been primarily working in still photography will learn to transition to creating with moving images by addressing time, structure, sound, and installation. Advanced discussions on film and digital formats, quality of image, camera support systems, and post-production will be explored through a combination of screenings, assignments, and readings.",
