    desc: "Field-intensive course focusing on issues relevant to the ecology of the arctic regions. Explores the changing arctic environment through lectures and hands-on research during an 18-day camping trip transecting the subarctic boreal forest to the high Arctic. Enrollment is by permission of the instructor. Prerequisite(s): BIOL 20A , and BIOE 20B and BIOE 20C ; and concurrent enrollment BIOE 153A and BIOE 153C .",
