    desc: "Designed to give students practical experience with contemporary research topics, methods and skills in linguistics and the broader language sciences. Students engage directly with local researchers and conduct targeted in-class skills activities. Students complete a portfolio of assignments which allow them to broaden their understanding of potential research areas in linguistics and language sciences and also to develop a particular topic of interest, culminating in a literature review and project proposal. Enrollment is by permission of the instructor.",
