    units: 5, division: "upper",
    prereqs: [],
    ge: "IM", quarters: ["F", "W", "S"],
    desc: "Addresses questions such as: \"How do popular conceptions of beauty serve state power or resist it?” “Is art always political?” “Does politics always involve an aesthetic dimension?” Course considers a range of material including texts, images, statues, architecture, and music (e.g., Pyramids, Great Wall, Mount Rushmore). Prior coursework in political theory recommended.",
