    ge: "CC", quarters: ["F", "W", "S"],
    desc: "Examines the material, discursive, and racialized conditions that have produced refugees in the last century. Also examines the social claims made by refugees, institutional responses to them, and political alternatives to state belonging",
    section: ["FREE"], rmpScore: 0
